{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "8f35f4d4-6f84-4c54-a519-c5de9bd68d15",
    "name": "AAA API",
    "description": "Collection Postman pour l'API AAA Laravel.\n\nAuthentification disponible :\n- Bearer Token JWT pour Postman / client lourd\n- Cookie JWT HttpOnly pour un client web\n\nEndpoints couverts:\n- Authentification\n- Utilisateurs\n- Roles\n- Permissions\n\nCompte admin seedé:\n- email: admin@example.com\n- password: Admin123!\n\nUtilisation conseillée:\n1. Importer la collection et l'environnement local\n2. Lancer Login Admin pour charger le token JWT\n3. Tester les endpoints users/roles/permissions\n4. Lancer Register User ou Create User pour créer un utilisateur de test et récupérer son user_id\n\nNote : la collection utilise surtout le mode Bearer Token. Pour le mode cookie web, les requêtes write doivent envoyer X-CSRF-TOKEN avec la valeur du cookie XSRF-TOKEN.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Auth",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Register User",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.environment.set('generated_user_email', 'student+' + Date.now() + '@example.com');"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Status code is 201', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(201);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "if (json.data && json.data.token) {",
                  "    pm.environment.set('auth_token', json.data.token);",
                  "    pm.environment.set('user_id', json.data.user.id);",
                  "    pm.environment.set('user_email', json.data.user.email);",
                  "    pm.environment.set('current_user_id', json.data.user.id);",
                  "    pm.environment.set('current_user_email', json.data.user.email);",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              },
              {
                "key": "Accept",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"{{generated_user_name}}\",\n  \"email\": \"{{generated_user_email}}\",\n  \"password\": \"{{generated_user_password}}\",\n  \"password_confirmation\": \"{{generated_user_password}}\"\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/auth/register",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "auth",
                "register"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Crée un utilisateur de test et stocke automatiquement le token, l'user_id et l'email dans l'environnement."
          },
          "response": []
        },
